<div class="badge error-badge">❌ Deployment Failed</div>

<h1 class="title">Deployment Failed</h1>
<p class="subtitle">Unfortunately, your deployment for <strong>{{projectName}}</strong> has failed. Don't worry - we'll help you get it fixed.</p>

<div class="feature-list">
  <h3>Deployment Details</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Project:</strong> {{projectName}}</li>
    <li><strong>Environment:</strong> {{environment}}</li>
    <li><strong>Failed:</strong> {{timestamp}}</li>
    {{#if errorMessage}}
    <li><strong>Error:</strong> <span style="color: #fecaca;">{{errorMessage}}</span></li>
    {{/if}}
    {{#if commitHash}}
    <li><strong>Commit:</strong> {{commitHash}}</li>
    {{/if}}
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="security-info">
  <strong>Next Steps:</strong> Check the deployment logs for detailed error information, verify your configuration, and try deploying again. Our support team is here to help if needed.
</div>

{{#if logsUrl}}
{{> button url=logsUrl label="View Deployment Logs"}}
{{/if}}

{{#if dashboardUrl}}
<p style="color: #737373; margin: 24px 0 0 0; font-size: 14px; text-align: center;">
  <a href="{{dashboardUrl}}" class="text-link">Go to Project Dashboard</a> • 
  <a href="mailto:support@deployio.tech" class="text-link">Contact Support</a>
</p>
{{/if}}
